<br>
Fluffy if a Standard 9.4k Black Rope Whip Horse. I don't use her for speed, my Jboots are faster. However, her other abilities are definately worth the cost.<br>
<br>
Your always medding while on a horse. Your Medding while running, fighting, casting, banking, ect. You gain no aggro while medding.<br>
<br>
This can be used incredible well in 2 ways. First off, Chaincasting. Your can med, 100% of the time, no aggro. This makes switching from 1 pet to another easy. Also it makes using Right Clicky items like Velious Robes and Pants easier, your medding the whole time.<br>
<br>
However, I have another approach in which i use my horse for. I'm sure most of you know what Aggro Kiting is. Piss off the mob with a big spell, turn taunt off, and kite till the mob is killed by your pet. I can constantly kill because I am constantly regenerating mana. I can't wait till 54 and the backstabbing pet to help with this.<br>
<br>
Now, soloing is dependant on my mana, correct? Here is how I &quot;Med up while getting another kill&quot;.<br>
<br>
First off, find a nice outdoor zone, ME for example. Kill a mob chaincasting like you normally would. This takes what, 2 or 3 bars of mana? Keep 1 Bar, when you have that 1 bar use it to piss off a mob, and Aggro kite it. The Advantage here is you get experience during a time in which you'll normally be medding. By the time the mob is dead, your FM. <p>"History is just a set of lies agreed upon" - Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte
